sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in DaVita Inc (Symbol: DVA), where a total of 16,203 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 1.6 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 76.1% of DVA's average daily trading volume over the past month of 2.1 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $72.50 strike call option expiring January 18, 2019 , with 6,014 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 601,400 underlying shares of DVA.

Juniper Networks Inc (Symbol: JNPR) options are showing a volume of 19,729 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 2.0 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 46.7% of JNPR's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $28.50 strike call option expiring November 30, 2018 , with 5,664 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 566,400 underlying shares of JNPR.

Below is a chart showing JNPR's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $28.50 strike highlighted in orange:

And Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD) saw options trading volume of 28,621 contracts, representing approximately 2.9 million underlying shares or approximately 46.1% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 6.2 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $172.50 strike call option expiring November 30, 2018 , with 3,874 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 387,400 underlying shares of HD.
